{
  "stem": "7546.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well when hell started, when the Germans came, grabbing people in the middle of the street, taking them to all kind of jobs that was terribly humiliating, my father decided-- he called my brother and me into the house, and he says, look, you're big enough to realize that there's danger here.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, a lot of people are going to go over to the Russian zone.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because, as you know, Ribbentrop and Stalin wrote a pact.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They became friends all of a sudden.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they divided Poland in half, and the border was a river called Bug, B-U-G.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And since a lot of youngsters and older people started running away from the Germans into the Russian zone, my father decided that the crown of his life, his two sons, since my three sisters were married already, just let them save their lives and run into the Russian zone.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He gave us-- each one of us had five gold coins, Russian gold coins that somehow he had it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I never knew he had them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But they were sewn in by my mother into the belts of our pants.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We had, each one of us, my brother and I, had five gold Russian coins, so that when we get into the Russian zone, we should be able to buy food, or even buy our lives with it, if need be.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Well, we took the train.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We had to rig a wagon.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Finally at night, we came in front of the river Bug, which was the borderline between German-- the German army and the Russian army.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And you had to buy somebody.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "In other words, you had a lot of Poles used to have handmade boats.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
